name: Michigan
blurb: Looked slightly human against Penn State but don't see them getting a challenge until Nebraska on Jan 27.

name: Purdue
blurb: Continuing to stack wins in a very workmanlike fashion. Nothing flashy but getting the job done.

name: Michigan State
blurb: Jaxon Kohler is shooting over 50% from three!

name: Illinois
blurb: Defense has gotten back on track since Nebraska but can they prevent Bennett Stirtz from going for 30?

name: Nebraska
blurb: Braden Frager has emerged as a potential third option scoring wise and that is a big development.

name: Iowa
blurb: The game against Minnesota was lost when Stirtz was on the bench with foul trouble. It's an obvious statement but they aren't very good without him.

name: Wisconsin
blurb: The trio of Boyd-Blackwell-Winter is pretty good but what's behind that is terrible.

name: Indiana
blurb: Indiana isn't so good that Tucker DeVries can disappear in conference games.

name: UCLA
blurb: Will Mick Cronin ever get his guys to show up on the road?

name: Washington
blurb: Looking more an more like Danny Sprinkle is going to squander a really good roster.

name: Ohio State
blurb: Christoph Tilly has been a major disappointment.

name: Minnesota
blurb: Frankly surprised that this team was able to close down the win against Iowa. Not sure a Ben Johnson coached team gets that done..

name: Northwestern
blurb: The pieces around Nick Martinelli have not materialized and time is running out.

name: USC
blurb: Muss couldn't get out of the state of Michigan fast enough.

name: Penn State
blurb: Didn't get the results they wanted recently but showed they will not get punked at home.

name: Maryland
blurb: Next years recruiting class can't come soon enough.

name: Rutgers
blurb: Need a fresh start at head coach. The offensive philosophy is well overdue for a change.
